# Sonar dedup enforcer (offer only)

The duplication prescan skill (`sonar-duplication-prescan`) is **explicit-only** (`disable-model-invocation: true`).

## After completing work

When you finish a turn that **edited source code** under `apps/` or `packages/`:

1. Do **not** run the prescan automatically.
2. End with a **one-line offer**, e.g. *Want me to run `/sonar-duplication-prescan` on these changes?*
3. If the user says yes, read and follow `.cursor/skills/sonar-duplication-prescan/SKILL.md`.

## When to skip the offer

- Question-only or review-only turns (no edits)
- Docs-only, lockfile-only, or generated-file-only changes
- The user already ran or declined a prescan in the same thread
- Trivial one-line edits with no duplication risk

Keep the offer brief — one sentence, no bullet list.
